Automation Tools:
    - we can develop the UI Applications like angularjs , angular4, reactJS , d3js,...with the help of following
      Automation tools.

      1. bower
      2. Gulp
      3. Karma with Jasmine

bower:

    bower is the Automation tool used to download the dependencies to develop web application

    bower based on NodeJS

installation of bower:
----------------------
>npm install -g bower


bower components:
-----------------

1. bower.json

2. .bowerrc



bower.json
-
    - this component used to mention the required dependencies to develop web application.


bower.json
----------
{
    "name":"nareshit",
    "dependencies":{
        "angular":"latest",
        "bootstrap":"latest"
    }
}

.bowerrc
--------

    - this component used to mention the path to dependencies downloading by bower.

{
    "directory":"bower_components"
}




installation of bower components
--------------------------------
> bower install

[Note : when ever we install the bower components , automatically "angular&bootstrap" frameworks
        will downloads to "bower_components" folder(directory)].

        **************************
bower_components
    angular
        angular.min.js

    bootstrap
        dist
            css
                bootstrap.min.css
    jquery
        dist
            jquery.min.js
         *************************

index.html
-
<html>

    <script src="bower_components/angular/angular.min.js"></script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="bower_components/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <script src="bower_components/jquery/dist/jquery.min.js"></script>
</html>


commands in bower:
------------------
1. bower list

    - it will return all the dependencies with versions available in web application.

2. bower uninstall bootstrap --save

    - it will uninstall the bootstrap and updates the bower.json file automatically.

3. bower install jquery --save

    - it will download jquery latest version and updates the bower.json file automatically.



Gulp:
----
    - Gulp is the production tool , used to perform the following operations on UI Projects.


    1. Concat the files.

    2. Uglify the JS, HTML , CSS files. (Compress)

    3. warm up the servers.

    4. open the browsers

    5. conversion of LESS & SASS to CSS files.

    6. Detecting the front end application changes.

    7. live reloading the browsers.


installation of gulp:
---------------------
> npm install -g gulp


Gulp Component:
---------------
    - package.json

        - by using package.json file we can download gulp related modules.














